Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:04.48,Festival,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Suzuki Balloon Festival\N{\fs16}{\c&H343F52&}First Prize 10 Million Yen
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.53,0:00:23.21,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,There are hot air balloons everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.49,0:00:25.32,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,I know. They're so pretty.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.32,0:00:28.63,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,This is the nation's biggest \Nhot air balloon rally.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.84,0:00:32.72,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,The first place winner will \Nreceive a 10 million yen prize.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.72,0:00:34.01,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.01,0:00:34.98,HQ,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Event Headquarters
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.85,0:00:45.52,Reception,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Reception
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.86,0:00:36.44,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Hasegawa-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.64,0:00:40.97,DCMain,HASEGAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Miss, thank you for coming \Nall the way out here.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.97,0:00:43.16,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,I brought a friend this year.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.16,0:00:44.02,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,That's okay, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.02,0:00:45.52,DCMain,HASEGAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, that's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.81,0:00:51.32,Ayato,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,250)}Hasegawa Ayato (45)
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.91,0:00:48.61,DCMain,HASEGAWA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I'm Hasegawa of the event \Nmanagement committee.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.61,0:00:51.78,DCMain,HASEGAWA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}We'll take all the guests we can get.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.05,0:00:56.03,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, how high can a hot air balloon fly?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.03,0:00:58.36,DCMain,HASEGAWA,0000,0000,0000,,It depends on the size of the balloon.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.36,0:01:02.46,DCMain,HASEGAWA,0000,0000,0000,,But the larger ones have climbed \Nover 10 thousand meters in the air.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.76,0:01:05.35,DCMain,HASEGAWA,0000,0000,0000,,They can easily fly above Mt. Fuji.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.35,0:01:07.54,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Really? I'd like to ride one!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.12,0:01:10.90,DCMain,HASEGAWA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to be riding one to \Nrecord the event on video.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.90,0:01:12.05,DCMain,HASEGAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Would you like to ride with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.78,0:01:14.36,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.36,0:01:17.55,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You guys should ride with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.76,0:01:19.70,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,But we'd be bothering him.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.70,0:01:20.55,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.55,0:01:24.06,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You're actually just scared, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.42,0:01:26.70,DCMain,HASEGAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Hot air balloons are safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.70,0:01:28.50,DCMain,HASEGAWA,0000,0000,0000,,You'll be totally fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.14,0:01:31.76,DCMain,HASEGAWA,0000,0000,0000,,They're as large as a seven story \Nbuilding and full of light air.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.76,0:01:34.66,DCMain,HASEGAWA,0000,0000,0000,,It takes more than a tiny hole
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.66,0:01:37.86,DCMain,HASEGAWA,0000,0000,0000,,to make them fall out of the sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.86,0:01:39.07,DCMain,MIZUGUCHI,0000,0000,0000,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.46,0:01:41.71,DCMain,MIZUGUCHI,0000,0000,0000,,Did you hear what the event manager said?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.71,0:01:44.08,DCMain,HASEGAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Mizuguchi-san, is something wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.43,0:01:47.69,DCMain,MIZUGUCHI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I just came to register another person.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.66,0:01:50.29,Shingo,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,250)}Mizuguchi Shingo (37)
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.19,0:01:51.59,DCMain,MIZUGUCHI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I want to show my wife the view from above.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.59,0:01:55.15,DCMain,ARISA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I'd been turning down his \Ninvitations until now.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.00,0:01:57.09,Arisa,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,250)}Mizuguchi Arisa (33)
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.15,0:01:57.47,DCMain,ARISA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}But I thought I'd try riding one this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.94,0:01:58.84,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.84,0:02:02.97,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,If you miss this chance, you're \Nnot likely to get one again.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.43,0:02:09.90,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,A canvas stained black with crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.43,0:02:12.48,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,With brilliant detective \Nskills, its color is changed!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.04,0:02:15.00,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Giant and colorful hot air balloons.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.00,0:02:17.06,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But something unexpected \Noccurs while riding one.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.06,0:02:20.84,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Always determining the one truth with the \Nbody of a child and the mind of an adult,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.84,0:02:23.28,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,his name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.97,0:04:08.97,DCEpTitle,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(398,1)}Mystery in a Hot Air Balloon
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.88,0:04:06.17,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,"Mystery in a Hot Air Balloon!"
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.97,0:04:13.75,DCMain,ARISA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not actually very interested \Nin hot air balloons.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.75,0:04:15.98,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,What? Why'd you agree to ride, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.98,0:04:17.87,DCMain,ARISA,0000,0000,0000,,He wanted me to accept the champion's cup,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.87,0:04:20.70,DCMain,ARISA,0000,0000,0000,,since he was so confident he'd win.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.70,0:04:23.99,DCMain,ARISA,0000,0000,0000,,And he said he'd buy me a \Nnecklace with the prize money.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.41,0:04:26.06,DCMain,ARISA,0000,0000,0000,,So I agreed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.44,0:04:30.37,DCMain,ARISA,0000,0000,0000,,Because he flies hot air \Nballoons on his meager salary,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.37,0:04:33.32,DCMain,ARISA,0000,0000,0000,,he hardly buys me any accessories.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.64,0:04:36.50,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.50,0:04:37.54,DCMain,MIZUGUCHI,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.54,0:04:38.75,DCMain,MIZUGUCHI,0000,0000,0000,,Don't do it! Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.06,0:04:42.38,DCMain,OKUDA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}There's no way you'd beat me!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.09,0:04:42.38,Akihiro,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,1)}Okuda Akihiro (35)
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.61,0:04:43.72,DCMain,MIZUGUCHI,0000,0000,0000,,What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.02,0:04:45.47,DCMain,MIZUGUCHI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm the champion!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.63,0:04:47.00,DCMain,OKUDA,0000,0000,0000,,So what?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.00,0:04:47.88,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.08,0:04:49.24,DCMain,ARISA,0000,0000,0000,,Darling.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.89,0:04:51.81,DCMain,ARISA,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing? Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.10,0:04:52.81,DCMain,ARISA,0000,0000,0000,,Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.26,0:04:55.64,DCMain,MIZUGUCHI,0000,0000,0000,,Arisa. But heâ€”
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.64,0:04:57.06,DCMain,OKUDA,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.06,0:04:59.06,DCMain,OKUDA,0000,0000,0000,,You're the one who started it!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.30,0:05:01.33,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,I thought hot air ballooning...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.33,0:05:04.17,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,...was a more laid-back activity.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.59,0:05:07.07,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like it isn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.93,0:05:12.08,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Mizuguchi-san said he was the champion.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.33,0:05:13.44,DCMain,HASEGAWA,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.44,0:05:15.96,DCMain,HASEGAWA,0000,0000,0000,,He's been the reigning \Nchampion two years in a row.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.96,0:05:17.98,DCMain,HASEGAWA,0000,0000,0000,,He's a very passionate man.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.98,0:05:20.60,DCMain,HASEGAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Last night he was here working on his balloon
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.60,0:05:22.42,DCMain,HASEGAWA,0000,0000,0000,,after the rest of us had \Ngone back to the hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.55,0:05:24.32,DCMain,HASEGAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Look.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.32,0:05:27.80,DCMain,HASEGAWA,0000,0000,0000,,The blue balloon all the way \Nover there is Mizuguchi-san's.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.22,0:05:30.74,DCMain,ANNOUNCE,0000,0000,0000,,Please get ready to start.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.87,0:05:55.72,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,I-It's amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.72,0:05:57.18,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's so pretty...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.30,0:06:01.75,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, look!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.07,0:06:04.67,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The people are getting smaller.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.67,0:06:06.51,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.47,0:06:49.00,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone else is leaving us behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.00,0:06:50.88,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Do we not have to go after them?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.88,0:06:51.60,DCMain,HASEGAWA,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.60,0:06:54.15,DCMain,HASEGAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like the wind is stronger up above.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.76,0:06:57.61,DCMain,HASEGAWA,0000,0000,0000,,I'll man the burner, so you \Ntake the camera, Conan-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.61,0:06:57.98,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.24,0:06:59.02,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.88,0:07:01.13,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Is something wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.13,0:07:03.11,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.38,0:07:09.56,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone's going so fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.56,0:07:12.54,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it dangerous for them \Nto be flying so close?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.54,0:07:16.72,DCMain,HASEGAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Today's task is called a "race to area."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.12,0:07:21.68,DCMain,HASEGAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Participants score points not just for \Ndropping the marker on the target,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.68,0:07:23.57,DCMain,HASEGAWA,0000,0000,0000,,but also for speed.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.57,0:07:27.00,DCMain,HASEGAWA,0000,0000,0000,,So everyone's trying to reach the \Nfinish line as quickly as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.23,0:07:29.53,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that dangerous?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.53,0:07:30.48,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Where?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.48,0:07:32.94,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,The blue balloon in the lead.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.94,0:07:34.32,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,There are two people riding.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.32,0:07:36.26,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that Mizuguchi-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.74,0:07:40.27,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Watch out! They're going to crash!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.13,0:07:49.99,DCMain,HASEGAWA,0000,0000,0000,,He opened the deflation port!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.94,0:07:54.41,DCMain,HASEGAWA,0000,0000,0000,,He's trying to run towards the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.24,0:08:04.29,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,They're falling.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.29,0:08:07.30,DCMain,HASEGAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, but hot air balloons fall slowly.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.30,0:08:09.07,DCMain,HASEGAWA,0000,0000,0000,,The people riding should be okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.25,0:08:27.31,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.24,0:08:41.12,DCMain,MIZUGUCHI,0000,0000,0000,,Arisa...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.72,0:08:43.35,DCMain,MIZUGUCHI,0000,0000,0000,,How could this happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.72,0:08:51.01,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hasegawa-san, call the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.01,0:08:52.33,DCMain,HASEGAWA,0000,0000,0000,,G-Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.29,0:09:00.01,DCMain,KANEKO,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.24,0:09:04.44,DCMain,KANEKO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}It sounds like this was an accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.26,0:09:05.85,Kaneko,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,250)}Detective Kaneko (35) \NIbaraki Prefectural Police
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.99,0:09:07.52,DCMain,KANEKO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Where is the man piloting the \Nhot air balloon that hit them?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.52,0:09:10.64,DCMain,HASEGAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Okuda-san is still in the race.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.30,0:09:14.53,DCMain,HASEGAWA,0000,0000,0000,,He should be arriving at \Nthe finish line around now.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.89,0:09:15.87,DCMain,KANEKO,0000,0000,0000,,It may have been an accident,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.87,0:09:19.57,DCMain,KANEKO,0000,0000,0000,,but I'd like to know the particular \Ncircumstances that caused the woman to fall.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.28,0:09:26.01,DCMain,KANEKO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Kaneko of the Ibaraki Prefectural Police.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.01,0:09:27.92,DCMain,KANEKO,0000,0000,0000,,You're Mizuguchi Shingo-san, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.96,0:09:32.65,DCMain,KANEKO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry to have to ask \Nduring such a difficult time,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.65,0:09:36.38,DCMain,KANEKO,0000,0000,0000,,but could you describe what \Nhappened when your wife fell?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.93,0:09:42.54,DCMain,MIZUGUCHI,0000,0000,0000,,A hot air balloon crashed into ours \Nand tore a hole in the envelope.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.54,0:09:43.65,DCMain,KANEKO,0000,0000,0000,,The envelope?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.65,0:09:46.81,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's the balloon part on \Ntop of the hot air balloon.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.81,0:09:47.94,DCMain,KANEKO,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.94,0:09:49.06,DCMain,KANEKO,0000,0000,0000,,And then?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.06,0:09:50.76,DCMain,MIZUGUCHI,0000,0000,0000,,Because he crashed into us,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.76,0:09:52.65,DCMain,MIZUGUCHI,0000,0000,0000,,and the hole opened on \Nthe side of the balloon,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.13,0:09:54.59,DCMain,MIZUGUCHI,0000,0000,0000,,the basket shook.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.97,0:09:57.10,DCMain,MIZUGUCHI,0000,0000,0000,,I told her to hold on tight,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.79,0:09:59.16,DCMain,MIZUGUCHI,0000,0000,0000,,but Arisa...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.86,0:10:03.29,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,Sir, we're finished.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.29,0:10:05.50,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,Can we transport the body now?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.50,0:10:06.37,DCMain,KANEKO,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.60,0:10:07.53,DCMain,MIZUGUCHI,0000,0000,0000,,Arisa?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.00,0:10:09.88,DCMain,MIZUGUCHI,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you taking Arisa?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.04,0:10:13.06,DCMain,KANEKO,0000,0000,0000,,We may need to perform an autopsy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.06,0:10:14.50,DCMain,KANEKO,0000,0000,0000,,We're taking her to a university hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.77,0:10:17.00,DCMain,MIZUGUCHI,0000,0000,0000,,Please don't perform an autopsy on her!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.00,0:10:19.27,DCMain,MIZUGUCHI,0000,0000,0000,,How could you hurt her body even more?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.79,0:10:22.01,DCMain,MIZUGUCHI,0000,0000,0000,,She's already been hurt enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.24,0:10:25.34,DCMain,KANEKO,0000,0000,0000,,We know she died from the fall.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.80,0:10:30.02,DCMain,KANEKO,0000,0000,0000,,But until the coroner examines \Nher, we can't be sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.09,0:10:33.02,DCMain,MIZUGUCHI,0000,0000,0000,,Arisa!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.61,0:10:35.30,DCMain,MIZUGUCHI,0000,0000,0000,,Please take me with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.30,0:10:36.27,DCMain,KANEKO,0000,0000,0000,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.27,0:10:39.06,DCMain,KANEKO,0000,0000,0000,,You should probably get your \Ninjuries looked at, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.60,0:10:46.09,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,I felt so bad for them, I couldn't watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.09,0:10:49.33,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe he did this at our event.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.33,0:10:50.78,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,It may have been an accident,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.78,0:10:54.20,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,but Okuda won't get away with this.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.90,0:11:02.70,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.26,0:11:05.87,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Arisa-san's hat?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.74,0:11:09.04,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.84,0:11:13.36,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, Mizuguchi-san \Nhad a cut on his face.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.34,0:11:21.74,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Plastic?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.74,0:11:23.61,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Is that part of the balloon?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.21,0:11:25.56,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.32,0:11:28.54,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Sonoko says she's going to the finish line.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.76,0:11:29.98,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be right there.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.22,0:11:50.24,DCMain,OKUDA,0000,0000,0000,,She's dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.61,0:11:51.60,DCMain,OKUDA,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.60,0:11:55.01,DCMain,KANEKO,0000,0000,0000,,That's why the police are here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.01,0:11:57.02,DCMain,KANEKO,0000,0000,0000,,You really didn't know?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.02,0:11:58.44,DCMain,OKUDA,0000,0000,0000,,It's true!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.44,0:12:00.84,DCMain,OKUDA,0000,0000,0000,,I led the pack all the way here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.84,0:12:03.16,DCMain,OKUDA,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know what happened \Nto the guys in back.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.16,0:12:06.53,DCMain,KANEKO,0000,0000,0000,,So you acknowledge you crashed \Ninto Mizuguchi-san's balloon?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.70,0:12:09.37,DCMain,OKUDA,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, but it was a race.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.37,0:12:12.41,DCMain,OKUDA,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone was trying to get to the \Nfinish line as quickly as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.76,0:12:15.56,DCMain,OKUDA,0000,0000,0000,,This kind of thing happens \Nall the time in races.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.56,0:12:18.95,DCMain,KANEKO,0000,0000,0000,,It may have been an accident, \Nbut a person is dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.95,0:12:22.14,DCMain,KANEKO,0000,0000,0000,,You could be held accountable.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.14,0:12:23.68,DCMain,OKUDA,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.99,0:12:27.93,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Mister, you were fighting with Mizuguchi-san \Nbefore the race, weren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.13,0:12:28.70,DCMain,OKUDA,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.09,0:12:31.07,DCMain,KANEKO,0000,0000,0000,,What? Is that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.07,0:12:32.85,DCMain,OKUDA,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about, kid?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.16,0:12:36.35,DCItalic,OKUDA,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way you'd beat me!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.58,0:12:37.96,DCItalic,MIZUGUCHI,0000,0000,0000,,What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.96,0:12:39.78,DCItalic,MIZUGUCHI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm the champion!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.00,0:12:42.91,DCMain,OKUDA,0000,0000,0000,,I-It was his fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.91,0:12:45.78,DCMain,OKUDA,0000,0000,0000,,He said I was way too \Ninexperienced to beat him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.18,0:12:49.53,DCMain,KANEKO,0000,0000,0000,,So you got angry and deliberately \Nran into his balloon?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.94,0:12:51.95,DCMain,OKUDA,0000,0000,0000,,I said it wasn't on purpose!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.18,0:12:55.46,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,And part of your basket is broken.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.70,0:12:57.91,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Some of the wickerwork is sticking out.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.51,0:13:03.79,DCMain,KANEKO,0000,0000,0000,,He's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.36,0:13:07.04,DCMain,KANEKO,0000,0000,0000,,You tried to poke a hole \Nin Mizuguchi-san's balloon
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.04,0:13:08.97,DCMain,KANEKO,0000,0000,0000,,so he would drop out of the race.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.45,0:13:11.17,DCMain,KANEKO,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't an accident!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.48,0:13:12.97,DCMain,KANEKO,0000,0000,0000,,It's a murder!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.02,0:13:29.62,DCMain,KANEKO,0000,0000,0000,,And Okuda-san, you're the one who did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.81,0:13:30.66,DCMain,OKUDA,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.66,0:13:32.96,DCMain,OKUDA,0000,0000,0000,,D-Don't be ridiculous!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.96,0:13:34.62,DCMain,OKUDA,0000,0000,0000,,None of the cane was sticking out
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.98,0:13:37.10,DCMain,OKUDA,0000,0000,0000,,while I was working on \Nmy balloon yesterday!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.44,0:13:40.13,DCMain,OKUDA,0000,0000,0000,,A-And if he hadn't lowered his altitude,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.30,0:13:44.64,DCMain,OKUDA,0000,0000,0000,,our balloons would've just \Nbumped into each other!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.51,0:13:47.03,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.38,0:13:48.39,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,During the incident...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.53,0:13:54.31,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Mizuguchi-san opened the deflation \Nport and reduced his altitude.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.24,0:13:56.23,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.24,0:14:02.44,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Ran-neechan, you said "huh" \Nwhile we were flying, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.44,0:14:04.65,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Did you notice something strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.99,0:14:06.29,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.59,0:14:10.16,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,It looked like only one person was \Nriding in Mizuguchi-san's balloon.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.94,0:14:14.74,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,But when I looked later, \Nthere were two people there.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.74,0:14:16.84,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Arisa-san must have been \Ncrouching in the basket.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.94,0:14:22.32,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Hasegawa-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.32,0:14:23.70,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Can I see your camera?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.70,0:14:24.68,DCMain,HASEGAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.36,0:14:27.52,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.26,0:14:35.23,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.83,0:14:38.07,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.12,0:14:40.62,DCMain,KANEKO,0000,0000,0000,,In any case, Okuda-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.62,0:14:42.48,DCMain,KANEKO,0000,0000,0000,,you'll be coming to the station with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.65,0:14:46.17,DCMain,OKUDA,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a minute. I won today.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.17,0:14:49.65,DCMain,OKUDA,0000,0000,0000,,At least wait until after the award ceremony.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.10,0:15:07.46,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,That's all forensics has to report.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.46,0:15:09.04,DCMain,KANEKO,0000,0000,0000,,Good work.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.04,0:15:11.85,DCMain,KANEKO,0000,0000,0000,,Let me know if anything else comes up.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.85,0:15:12.65,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.19,0:15:19.43,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Mizuguchi-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.82,0:15:24.06,DCMain,KANEKO,0000,0000,0000,,Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.06,0:15:25.98,DCMain,MIZUGUCHI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.36,0:15:29.57,DCMain,MIZUGUCHI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry for causing so \Nmuch trouble at your event.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.57,0:15:32.06,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,It's not your fault, Mizuguchi-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.06,0:15:32.95,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.43,0:15:41.97,DCMain,HASEGAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Okuda-san, after meeting with the judges,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.97,0:15:46.18,DCMain,HASEGAWA,0000,0000,0000,,we've decided to revoke your victory \Nfor obstructing another competitor.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.18,0:15:47.92,DCMain,OKUDA,0000,0000,0000,,What? Obstructing?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.36,0:15:51.89,DCMain,OKUDA,0000,0000,0000,,I was just doing everything I could to win!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.89,0:15:53.89,DCMain,OKUDA,0000,0000,0000,,You've got to meet with the judges again!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.11,0:15:56.89,DCMain,HASEGAWA,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how many times we discuss \Nit, the result will be the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.19,0:16:03.07,DCMain,KANEKO,0000,0000,0000,,You heard him. Okuda-san, will \Nyou come to the station now?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.38,0:16:04.69,DCMain,OKUDA,0000,0000,0000,,B-But...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.80,0:16:15.91,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Sonoko, what's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.26,0:16:18.79,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Could you wait a minute, Detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.15,0:16:21.10,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Don't take him away yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.10,0:16:22.29,DCMain,KANEKO,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.60,0:16:26.92,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Because you should be arresting someone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.42,0:16:29.38,DCMain,KANEKO,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.26,0:16:33.73,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,The poor victim's husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.05,0:16:37.18,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Right, Mizuguchi Shingo-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.34,0:16:42.68,DCMain,MIZUGUCHI,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.06,0:16:48.34,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Hasegawa-san said last night \Nyou were the last one here
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.34,0:16:50.69,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,working on his balloon.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.20,0:16:57.57,DCNote,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Mizuguchi
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.83,0:17:05.62,DCNote,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Okuda
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.10,0:17:10.84,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,That's when you damaged the \Nbasket on Okuda-san's balloon
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.15,0:17:13.38,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,so the cane would stick out.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.56,0:17:20.00,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Then you provoked Okuda-san \Nbefore the race
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.00,0:17:22.20,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,so he would run into you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.83,0:17:26.10,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,If he hadn't, you probably meant \Nto run into him yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.66,0:17:30.02,DCMain,MIZUGUCHI,0000,0000,0000,,Why would I do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.42,0:17:33.40,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,When Ran looked inside \Nyour balloon in the air,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.40,0:17:36.60,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,she said she only saw one person.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.16,0:17:40.03,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,But the next time she \Nlooked, she saw two people.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.50,0:17:41.90,DCMain,MIZUGUCHI,0000,0000,0000,,Of course she did.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.90,0:17:43.66,DCMain,MIZUGUCHI,0000,0000,0000,,Two of us were in the balloon.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.66,0:17:44.87,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.87,0:17:46.28,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,There were two of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.00,0:17:51.54,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,But the person we saw wasn't Arisa-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.85,0:17:56.22,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Arisa-san was sitting in the basket.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.53,0:17:59.55,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,When I examined your \Nballoon on the riverbank,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.32,0:18:04.51,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,you had a bag containing the rope used
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.51,0:18:06.62,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,to lead the balloon when you land.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.05,0:18:10.51,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,But the bag containing another \Nimportant item was missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.02,0:18:14.80,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,And there was blood on \Nthe inside of the basket.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.60,0:18:19.45,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,At first I thought it got there \Nwhen you injured yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.27,0:18:24.58,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,But the blood was probably \Nyour wife Arisa-san's.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.58,0:18:28.40,DCMain,KANEKO,0000,0000,0000,,Forensics did say the blood \Nbelonged to the victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.40,0:18:31.42,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, Arisa-san was already injured
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.42,0:18:33.84,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,while riding in the balloon.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.22,0:18:43.05,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,When Okuda-san's balloon ran into yours,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.05,0:18:46.80,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,you had your arm around Arisa-san's body.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.23,0:18:51.77,DCMain,MIZUGUCHI,0000,0000,0000,,I was doing my best to protect \Nher in the unsteady basket!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.04,0:18:54.15,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,No, you weren't.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.57,0:18:58.15,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Watch out! They're going to crash!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.00,0:19:05.18,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,After opening the deflation port \Nand lowering your altitude,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.18,0:19:07.87,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,you were desperately holding down Arisa-san
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.87,0:19:10.37,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,so she wouldn't fly out of the basket.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.78,0:19:13.17,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Because that wasn't Arisa-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.17,0:19:16.20,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,It was a light inflatable doll.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.64,0:19:21.47,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,When you landed, in order \Nto destroy the evidence,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.47,0:19:24.11,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,you burned the doll along with the balloon.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.11,0:19:25.69,DCMain,MIZUGUCHI,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't stop,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.69,0:19:27.27,DCMain,MIZUGUCHI,0000,0000,0000,,I'll sue you for defamation!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.60,0:19:29.71,DCMain,MIZUGUCHI,0000,0000,0000,,It was an accident!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.71,0:19:33.21,DCMain,MIZUGUCHI,0000,0000,0000,,And if it wasn't an accident, \Nthen it was Okuda's fault!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.64,0:19:36.30,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,You don't know when to give up, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.74,0:19:39.46,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Now onto the main issue.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.88,0:19:45.73,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,After reducing your altitude and \Nhiding your basket from view,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.73,0:19:46.92,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,you...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.60,0:19:54.02,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,...threw the unconscious Arisa-san's \Nbody from the basket.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.27,0:20:07.96,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,You murdered Arisa-san who trusted you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.28,0:20:12.39,DCMain,MIZUGUCHI,0000,0000,0000,,She's lying!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.85,0:20:13.85,DCMain,MIZUGUCHI,0000,0000,0000,,She's making it all up!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.44,0:20:16.27,DCMain,MIZUGUCHI,0000,0000,0000,,Where's the proof?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.22,0:20:21.78,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Now, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.00,0:20:35.79,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Look at the burns on the balloon.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.12,0:20:37.20,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,If you look closely,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.20,0:20:41.30,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,there's some plastic stuck to the \Nballoon shaped like a doll's hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.09,0:20:44.87,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,And then there's this.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.87,0:20:49.10,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It was found about 300 meters \Nfrom the starting point.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.76,0:20:52.00,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,There's a fire extinguisher inside the bag.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.00,0:20:55.45,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It might match the wound on Arisa-san's head.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.88,0:21:01.46,DCMain,MIZUGUCHI,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't have a choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.73,0:21:06.83,DCMain,MIZUGUCHI,0000,0000,0000,,The stocks I bought with money \Nborrowed from my clients crashed.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.70,0:21:12.28,DCMain,MIZUGUCHI,0000,0000,0000,,If I didn't return it soon, they were \Ngoing to audit me next month.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.84,0:21:16.54,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,So you were blinded by your \Nwife's life insurance money.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.54,0:21:19.18,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,It's infuriating how stupid you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.58,0:21:23.59,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,You murdered someone just for the money.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.92,0:21:28.11,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,You should think about what you've \Ndone from inside a prison cell,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.11,0:21:29.62,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,you good-for-nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.47,0:21:35.74,DCMain,KANEKO,0000,0000,0000,,Mizuguchi-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.17,0:21:38.10,DCMain,KANEKO,0000,0000,0000,,please come with us to the station.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.25,0:23:13.26,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Way to go, Detective Queen.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.26,0:23:16.29,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That was really cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.29,0:23:18.79,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,R-Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.06,0:23:23.92,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't your detective skills \Napply to anything else?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.42,0:23:26.13,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,I don't need your concern.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.52,0:23:28.22,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,And when you're explaining your reasoning,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.22,0:23:31.06,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,why do you fall asleep like my dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.70,0:23:33.46,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You're right!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.46,0:23:36.47,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,If it's genetic, then you're \Nthe one who should be sleeping.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.34,0:23:39.05,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's not genetic.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.05,0:23:43.37,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Both of them are just sleeping, \Nnot solving mysteries.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.94,0:24:08.96,DCEpPreview,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Episode Preview
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.69,0:23:47.44,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's the voice of the tengu.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.76,0:23:51.30,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's so pretty.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.69,0:24:02.34,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Why was it shaking?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.74,0:24:04.64,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Probably because of the wind, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.28,0:24:08.96,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The voice of the tengu.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.96,0:24:14.97,DCNextEp,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,You Can Hear the Tengu's Voice
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.68,0:24:13.36,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The next episode of Conan is \N"You Can Hear the Tengu's Voice!"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.98,0:24:34.99,Hint,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Wind
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.77,0:24:33.01,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's hint!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.41,0:24:34.68,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The wind!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.99,0:24:39.99,Don'tMiss,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Don't miss the next episode.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.25,0:24:37.21,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}You can count on me to solve all cases!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.21,0:24:38.16,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I guess I went too far this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.16,0:24:39.78,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Sonoko is turning into a tengu.
